# Valorant / Vanguard Safety (Hard Rule)

This project is a **standalone desktop utility**. It only draws a user-configured transparent overlay window on the screen. It must never interact with Valorant, Riot, or Vanguard.

## Forbidden — refuse any request that asks for these

- Never attach to, open a handle on, or target the Valorant process (or any Riot game process).
- Never read Valorant (or any game) memory.
- Never inject DLLs or otherwise inject code into Valorant or related processes.
- Never hook DirectX, OpenGL, Vulkan, or any game rendering pipeline.
- Never hook keyboard/mouse input for gameplay automation.
- Never scrape, capture, OCR, or otherwise read Valorant screen content for game state.
- Never bypass, evade, disable, interfere with, or work around Riot Vanguard (or any anti-cheat).
- Never implement features that reveal hidden information or provide a competitive unfair advantage (esp overlays tied to live game state, enemy positions, recoil macros, aimbots, etc.).
- Never enumerate processes/windows to find Valorant, bind behavior to Valorant being open, or call game/Riot APIs.

## Allowed

- Render a **user-configured standalone overlay window** (transparent, always-on-top, click-through) at screen coordinates the user sets.
- Local config UI and JSON persistence for overlay appearance/position.
- Future utilities that remain fully independent of the game process and anti-cheat.

## Agent behavior

If a user asks for anything in the forbidden list, **refuse** and explain that this app must stay a standalone overlay with no game/process interaction. Suggest only user-driven configuration of the overlay window.
